# PauliBot: System Design & Proposed System Documentation

## D. System Design (Proposed System)

### Overview of the Proposed System
The **PauliBot** is an intelligent, AI-powered campus assistant designed specifically for St. Paul University Philippines (SPUP). Unlike traditional rule-based chatbots that rely on static keywords, PauliBot utilizes **Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)** to provide dynamic, context-aware, and highly accurate responses. 

The system serves as a 24/7 digital concierge, capable of answering complex inquiries about campus locations, staff directories, and university FAQs. By integrating the **Google Gemini API** with a dedicated local knowledge base, PauliBot ensures that students and guests receive information that is both linguistically natural and factually grounded in SPUP’s official data.

---

## F. Proposed System Description

### System Architecture
The PauliBot employs a modern, three-tier architecture designed for scalability, security, and high-performance AI inference.

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph Users ["Users"]
        Student_U["웃 Student"]
        Guest_U["웃 Guest"]
        Admin_U["웃 Admin"]
    end

    subgraph Client ["Presentation Layer (Front-end)"]
        UI["🌐 Web Browser<br/>(HTML / CSS / JS)"]
    end

    subgraph Server ["Logic Layer (Back-end)"]
        Django["🐍 Django Framework"]
        Logic["🧠 PauliBot Logic Engine"]
        RAG["🔍 RAG Searcher<br/>(SentenceTransformer)"]
    end

    subgraph AI ["External Services"]
        Gemini["🤖 Google Gemini API<br/>(Flash 2.5 Model)"]
    end

    subgraph DB ["Data Layer (Database)"]
        Postgres[("🐘 PostgreSQL + pgvector<br/>(Relational & Vector Data)")]
    end

    %% Flow of Data
    Users ==> UI
    UI <== HTTP ==> Django
    Django <==> Logic
    Logic <==> RAG
    RAG <==> Postgres
    Logic <== API Requests ==> Gemini
```

#### 1. Front-end (Presentation Layer)
-   **Technology**: Django Templates, Vanilla CSS, and JavaScript.
-   **Description**: A responsive web interface that provides a seamless chat experience. It handles user authentication (Student ID login), manages active conversation threads, and renders AI responses in real-time. The design prioritizes accessibility and ease of use for both desktop and mobile users.

#### 2. Back-end (Logic Layer)
-   **Technology**: Python / Django Framework.
-   **Core Components**:
    -   **PauliBot Logic Engine**: Orchestrates the communication between the user interface, the semantic searcher, and the Gemini API.
    -   **RAG Searcher**: Utilizes the `SentenceTransformer` model (`all-MiniLM-L6-v2`) to convert user queries into mathematical vectors.
    -   **Gemini API Integration**: Leverages Google’s Flash 2.5 model to synthesize the final response based on the retrieved campus context.

#### 3. Database (Data Layer)
-   **Technology**: PostgreSQL with **pgvector** extension.
-   **Storage**: 
    -   **Relational Data**: Stores user profiles, chat history, and administrative settings.
    -   **Vector Data**: Stores high-dimensional embeddings for the Knowledge Base (FAQs, Locations, and Staff details), enabling "semantic" searches that understand meaning rather than just matching words.

### How the New System Solves the Identified Problems

| Identified Problem | PauliBot Solution |
| :--- | :--- |
| **Information Overload** | Students often struggle to find specific info in handbooks. PauliBot provides **instant, direct answers** to specific questions. |
| **Staff Unavailability** | Inquiries after office hours or during busy periods go unanswered. PauliBot is **available 24/7**, relieving staff of repetitive queries. |
| **Outdated/Inaccurate Data** | Static websites are hard to update. The **Admin Dashboard** allows staff to update the knowledge base instantly, which the AI immediately learns. |
| **Keyword Limitations** | Traditional bots fail if the user doesn't use exact words. PauliBot's **Semantic Search** understands intent (e.g., "Where is the registrar?" vs. "registrar's office location"). |
| **Misinformation (AI Hallucinations)** | General Lexical AI can make things up. PauliBot’s **RAG approach** forces the AI to answer *only* using verified SPUP data. |

